public class MeasureListType
extends java.lang.Object

List of numbers with a uniform scale. The value of uom (Units Of Measure) attribute is a reference to a Reference System for the amount, either a ratio or position scale.

Java class for MeasureListType complex type.

getValue

public java.util.List<java.lang.Double> getValue()
XML List based on XML Schema double type. An element of this type contains a space-separated list of double values Gets the value of the value property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the value property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getValue().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Double
